%U A394664 1,4,3,0,3,4,0,0,7,0,2,0,2,1,4,1,7,5,9,7,2,6
%N A394664 Decimal expansion of the constant characterizing the complexity of Coppersmith's version of the general number field sieve (GNFS) factoring algorithm.
%C A394664 The Coppersmith's version of the GNFS algorithm has complexity O(exp(c*(log(n))^(1/3)*(log(log(n))^(2/3)))), where c is the present constant.
%H A394664 Paolo Xausa, <a href="/A394664/b394664.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000</a>
%H A394664 Don Coppersmith, <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/BF00198464">Modifications to the Number Field Sieve</a>, Journal of Cryptology, Volume 6, 1993, pp. 169-180 (see p. 177).
%H A394664 Carl Pomerance, <a href="https://www.ams.org/notices/199612/pomerance.pdf">A Tale of Two Sieves</a>, Notices of the American Mathematical Society, Volume 43, Number 12, December 1996, pp. 1473-1485 (see p. 1482).
%H A394664 Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, <a href="https://mathworld.wolfram.com/NumberFieldSieve.html">Number Field Sieve</a>.
%F A394664 Equals (1/3)*(92 + 26*sqrt(13))^(1/3).
%e A394664 1.90188361186483941621457677238121331969038180799...
%t A394664 First[RealDigits[CubeRoot[92 + 26*Sqrt[13]]/3, 10, 100]]
%Y A394664 Cf. A394662, A394663.
%K A394664 nonn,cons,easy
